survey_response.review_text:
**** *********** ***** ******* ******** ******** *** ******** Charges high for such tests.

After seeing the older prescription of Dr Deepak Dutta Dr. Nagori gave my father the same medicine's as the previous doctor(Dr. Dutta) to whom my father used to go for checkup. What  Dr. S.B.Nagori did was asked my father to do few *********** tests after which the doctor said my father is fine and prescribed the exact same medicine's as the previous doctor. **** **** ********** ***** **** *** ******** **** ***** ***** ********* ** *** *********

I will say that Dr. S. B. Nagori is a humble person. He treats his patients equally either you belong to rich family or not . I would say that after consulting Dr. S. B.  Nagori I feel relaxed because he not only listened my health issues carefully, he just suggested for one test ECG only and have written few medicine which should be taken from any of the medical store available in the market. After the consultation with Dr.  S. B.  Nagori I feel that he is one of the best cardiologist in Kolkatta who will never force you for unwanted test's and medicine which is not necessary for you. He just suggests whatever is necessary for your diagnosis . So I would really recommend Dr. S. B. Nagori to everyone who are suffering from any heart issues should must visit once Dr. S.B. Nagori . you will not only get best treatment, you will save your lots of money too.

Treatment methodology of Dr. Nagori sir is great as he starts someone's treatment from the base then he proceed to advance level . He will definitely diagnose you with some other tests but trust me if he's recommending some tests that means the patient is going though a thorough check up under his supervision and rest assured. No doubt, from now on he's and will be a highly recommend doctor from my side. The staffs of CHRC are also cordial and always ready with their assistance to all. Thank you for the nice experience.

review_reply.reply_text: The patient had already got done a CT Angiogram of the Heart. He was insistent on whether he should go for a coronary angiogram or not and asked me to answer this specifically. Nothing else. The current position of the heart of any patient can only be known by an ECG (which by the way costs only Rs 300/-). I complied with the patient’s requirement of advising a coronary angiogram. To prescribe medicine, I need a basic diagnosis and ECG is an important part of it. If the patient comes to me with a current ECG, I am willing to provide consultation for free.
